race.comment: QUEEN AVENGER (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Bendigo behind Nigel Devere (28.35) in a Grade 4/5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from four starts. Top prospect. PETE'S ENTITY (8) goes very well over this track and trip including two wins. Hit the frame latest (25.88) when third at Ballarat in a Grade 5. Among the main chances. HOT SAKI (2) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (22.61) in a Grade 5 at Warrnambool. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. The form out of his last race has been franked. Should be in this for a long way. FEDERAL HAVANA (3) must be respected as a past winner at this course and distance.
